Class ProcessType

    This class contains methods for a Process Type, a Simpplle Type.

    It contains methods for database, then a set of constants which define the different process type, and methods.

      • ProcessType

        protected ProcessType(java.lang.String processName,
           java.lang.String className,
           boolean spreading)
        Overloaded constructor. Initializes process and class name, and spreading to passed in arguments. example. the following is a process type dissected below. public static final ProcessType DEBRIS_EVENT = new ProcessType("DEBRIS-EVENT","DebrisEvent",false); DEBRIS_EVENT (variable name) "DEBRIS-EVENT" - process name "DebrisEvent" - className false - spreading

      • isFireLessIntense

        public boolean isFireLessIntense(ProcessType p)
        Calculates intensity of fires.
        Parameters:
        p - the process type. this should be either SRF - stand replacing fire or MSF mixed severity fire. any other input will return false
        Returns:
        the levels of fire in decreasing order are SRF, MSF and LSF. This method returns true if input fire type is less intense then current.
